9.body:
Task Solution Encode a string to URL There is no dedicated method implemented within std, rely on the crates. Consider urlencoding and utl , for example. They both are doing encoding on the binary data representation with relying on the URL spec . Do no see any practical use of any attempts to implemen this logic on the application level. use urlencoding::encode; let input = "https://music.yandex.ru/album/2459398/track/21484345";
println!("{}", urlencoding::encode(input)); // https%3A%2F%2Fmusic.yandex.ru%2Falbum%2F2459398%2Ftrack%2F21484345
